#compdef maelstrom-go-test
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# maelstrom-software/maelstrom ‚Äî
#   crates/maelstrom-go-test/src/config.rs lines 4-50
#     (Config flattening TestRunnerConfig + adding
#     GoTestConfig with 4 Go-test-specific flags)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# maelstrom-go-test is the **distributed-execution Go test
# runner** from maelstrom-software ‚Äî sister to R238's cargo-
# maelstrom (Rust) and R239's maelstrom-pytest (Python).
# Runs `go test` workloads across a fleet of broker + worker
# machines.  Inherits all 22 test-runner flags from R238 via
# the flattened TestRunnerConfig parent (at config.rs:6-7)
# and ADDS 4 Go-test-specific flags at config.rs:14-36.
#
# Critical extraction note: GoTestConfig at lines 13-36 has
# 4 flags decoded source-direct from the `go test` and `go
# help testflag` documentation:
#   --vet VET-OPTIONS    forwards to `go test -vet=...`
#                        (e.g. "off", "all", "shadow,unreachable")
#   --short              forwards to `go test -short`
#                        (run only short tests)
#   --fullpath           forwards to `go test -fullpath`
#                        (show full file names in errors)
#   --extra-test-binary-args
#                        var_arg trailing variadic ‚Äî anything
#                        after this flag is passed to the
#                        compiled test binary (e.g.
#                        `-test.bench` `-test.cpuprofile`)
# Same `#[config(flatten)]` composition pattern as
# R239's maelstrom-pytest.
#
# Critical extraction note: maelstrom-go-test has 2
# `#[config(flag)]` boolean toggles (`short`, `fullpath`) ‚Äî
# adds 2 to the corpus's `#[config(flag)]` documentation
# started in R238 (cargo-maelstrom's `--accept-invalid-
# remote-container-tls-certs`).

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help and exit]' \
  '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[show version and exit]' \
  '(-L --log-level)'{-L+,--log-level=}'[(inherited) min log level]:level:(error warn info debug trace)' \
  '--ui=[(inherited) UI style]:style:(auto simple quiet fancy)' \
  '(-r --repeat --loop)'{-r+,--repeat=,--loop=}'[(inherited) repeat each test N times]:count:' \
  '(-s --stop-after)'{-s+,--stop-after=}'[(inherited) stop after N failures]:num:' \
  '(-t --timeout)'{-t+,--timeout=}'[(inherited) override timeout in seconds]:seconds:' \
  '(-b --broker)'{-b+,--broker=}'[(inherited) broker socket addr (standalone if absent)]:sockaddr:' \
  '--cluster-communication-strategy=[(HIDDEN; inherited) tcp or github]:strategy:(tcp github)' \
  '--github-actions-token=[(HIDDEN; inherited) ACTIONS_RUNTIME_TOKEN]:token:' \
  '--github-actions-url=[(HIDDEN; inherited) ACTIONS_RESULTS_URL]:url:_urls' \
  '--cache-size=[(inherited) local worker cache size]:bytes:' \
  '--inline-limit=[(inherited) max bytes returned inline for stdout/stderr]:bytes:' \
  '--slots=[(inherited) number of job slots]:n:' \
  '--container-image-depot-root=[(inherited) container image cache directory]:path:_files -/' \
  '--accept-invalid-remote-container-tls-certs[(inherited) accept invalid TLS for container images]' \
  \*{-i+,--include=}'[(inherited) include filter (repeatable; default "all")]:filter:' \
  \*{-x+,--exclude=}'[(inherited) exclude filter (repeatable)]:filter:' \
  '--init[(inherited) write starter test metadata file then exit]' \
  '(-w --watch)'{-w,--watch}'[(inherited) watch mode]' \
  '--client-process[(HIDDEN; inherited) internal testing flag]' \
  '--vet=[forwarded to `go test -vet=...` (e.g. off|all|shadow|unreachable)]:vet:(off all shadow unreachable assign atomic bools buildtag composites errorsas httpresponse ifaceassert loopclosure lostcancel nilfunc printf shift slog stdmethods stringintconv structtag testinggoroutine tests unmarshal unsafeptr unusedresult)' \
  '--short[forwarded to `go test -short` (run only short tests)]' \
  '--fullpath[forwarded to `go test -fullpath` (show full file names in errors)]' \
  '*::extra-test-binary-args (var_arg; all remaining argv passed to the compiled test binary):'
